To all and every the constables of St. Clements Danes of the Dutchy Liberty, of Covent-garden, and St. Martins in the Fields Throckmorton, William.
1 sheet ([1] p.)
Printed by John Bill, Printer to the King's most Excellent Majesty, London : 1661.
An order of the Knight Marshall respecting regulations to be observed at the King's coronation. Dated and signed at end: Whitehall, by the authority above named, the eight day of April, one thousand six hundred sixty one. William Throckmorton. Annotation on Thomason copy: "April 9". Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
